profile_positions.description:
In this role, I helped the New Energies Research and Technology team in creating opportunities and shaping strategies for our business in the field of power storage into molecules. I developed and executed a dedicated R&D program on electrochemistry, including building laboratory capabilities (E-Lab), and managed multiple external academic and industrial collaborations in the field. More specifically, my tasks were:

- program manager for all internal and external activities related to CO2 electrolysis and technical consultant for other Shell departments, e.g. Gamechanger, Chemicals and GTL;

- project manager of 5 R&D projects with leading academic institutions (11 PhDs and 5 PDs). To intensify collaboration between industry and academia, I set up several internships at Shell for PhD and Master students;

- manager of 2 internal projects focusing on improving the performance of CO2 electrolyzers, both guiding experimental work (2 experimentalists + students) and supporting the techno-economic analysis team.

During this role I've completed the Shell Graduate Program and Shell Advanced Technical Program,  focusing on technical and personal/leadership development including internal and external courses.
